rComments: This course is supposed to be one of the worst in the econ department, and while it was challenging, this prof makes it so much easier. Would highly recommend
Kindest, smartest, and most encouraging professor I have ever met.

If you have the chance, take Jason Garred. His explanations are so clear and his lectures are fun, even though he has to teach some dry concepts! Just great at teaching and simplifying difficult concepts. Best econ prof at UOttawa.

Taken this class a while ago. Jason is unbelievably committed in his teaching and has inspired many (including myself) to delve deeper into economics. He draws from very current literature, clearly explains methods and economic concepts, and fosters in-class participation without imposing pressure on students. See his name? Take that class!

really caring and nice! course is more focused on theory/data analysis than math. content is pretty abstract/confusing when ur in class, but just make sure to go over the notes. exams are just like previous ones. make sure to ask questions for clarification! no textbook required. stata can be a lil annoying.

Inspiring class with a great prof. Jason's class was my favourite undergrad course by far. He is exceptionally well organized and expectations are clear and fair. Course pacing is perfect. Lectures are interesting. No last minute cramming in of material before midterm/exam. Must attend classes to get full benefit. Highly recommend Jason as a prof!

Jason is a great professor. His expectations are clear and he is extremely patient with his students. He does not mind repeating himself just so you understand and he is available outside the class. He is very practical and he actually gets you thinking critically. The midterms are straight forward if you read and the assignments were great.

Jason is a fantastic prof. He really cares about the students and takes the time to learn everyone's names. His class required participation, but it amounted to an easy 10 percent of the final mark. He is enthusiastic and full of energy. The exams are easy if you read the material and pay attention in class. I recommend his classes 100%.
Best teacher ever.
My favourite econ prof so far. Funny, nice and really wants you to do well. His last assignment is difficult but exams are fair and he prepares you well for them .
very funny. His lecture is so clear and he is so nice!

He is so underrated! Jason is am amazing prof and I learned more in his class than with most profs. I feel that because he is such a great professor I will actually retain a lot of the info that I learned. Instead of learning theory, you learn the practical application which makes more sense because most students will only need the latter.

Professor Garred is hands-down the best economics prof I've had. He explains challenging material very well, has clear expectations, and is always available to help. Focused on conceptual aspects of econometrics which was really essential for practical applications. He's always cheerful and you can't help but to smile in his classes.

Jason is a really good professor. He cares about his students and hopes everyone to get good grades. Although his PPT includes everything, you still need to go to his class and skim through PPT with him. In fact, many concepts are difficult to understand for this course, but he can explained acceptably.

Jason takes what is one of the toughest classes in Econ and makes it accessible, applicable and interesting. Slides give you the info you need for studying while not being too wordy. Exams are exactly what he says they are. Assignments are different but interesting. He obviously cares and wants you to understand, will teach you in his office hours.

No doubt the best professor I've ever had. It is true that the workload is quite high but it's not because we're doing the job in his stead. He's always extremely well prepared and passionate about what he teaches. In addition, he is very accessible and available during and outside TA hours.

One of the best professors I've had! Interesting material that is actually applicable. Great to talk to, especially during office hours. Extremely helpful and clear with explanations. Always looked forward to class with him!
Jason's great. Amazing prof, very clear expectations. Would recommend in a heartbeat.

Hands down the best teacher I've had in my undergrad. He made it a point to learn and remember everybody's name. He is quirky/funny and is very current in pop culture. When he lectures, he's very enthusiastic. He treats everyone with respect. He never talks down to anyone. He cares about the well-being of his students. I could go on and on.

Hands down the best prof I've ever had. PPTs are short and very clear. Conveys subject matter amazingly. Will work with you to make sure you do well. Barely any reading too, you can do each classes reading in 3 min. I had him for Eco3151 too, course was a little harder but he still taught it great. Do yourself a favour and take any course of his.
Professor Garred presents otherwise dull and complex material in a relatively interesting and digestible manner. His exams are very fair and his assignments build necessary practical skills.
Jason takes a different approach to econometrics. He focuses on theory rather than the math behind it so it requires that you study hard. But if you do, it will pay off.

A must have prof. He's amazing! One of the best profs I have ever had. Makes the course interesting and you enjoy being in it. He teaches the material well and always answers questions when needed. He's always there to help his students out and really wants them to succeed. I really recommend having him.
